Renoen/Fefn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xaen>Xaen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://members.home.com/philipv1/oop.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333333>(6/3/01 12:15:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clive Barker's &quot;Undying&quot;</span><hr size=1> This game turned out to be one of my favorite Horror/FPS games. It really has some freaky moments, but twords the end, the game levels are some of the best i've ever seen in design and looks. The game tends to get better and better as you go along, but it could have used a bit more &quot;story&quot; I think. <br>
<br>
Oh, and it definately has some of the best weapons ever. One weapon you get (it's actually a spell, but counts as a weapon) is this skull that floats in your hand, and he cackles every now and then, and when a creature is near, the skull starts to scream and whine and flames shoot out of its eyes, and when you let go of the button, he flys off super fast with this evil laugh and explodes when he hits the target. It's just too damn fun using that spell in itself.. And you get this badass Scythe of the Celt and go around decapitating people all over, it gets pretty bloody. For hand to hand, it really rocked, sucked the life out of creatures and people. <br>
<br>
Oh, one other game to mention, if you LOVED the mindless Doom and Doom2 games where there were literally dozens and dozens of creatures on the screen with huge hulking beasts in between them stomping around trying to paste you - get <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  SERIOUS SAM</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. This is the best mindless blastathon I have ever played. It really stacks up next to the Doom games in all aspects. There are parts where there are literally 100+ creatures on the screen mobbing you, and you got badass chainguns and shit mowing them all down. Not to mention it has some decent humor .. Very little storyline, but playing this game was like playing Doom and Duke Nuken all over again for the first time! It was only $15 at Best Buy too (MEGA cheap!) .. GO BUY IT. Mindless splatterfest in the extreme!<br>
